    type='think',
    think='I see! The `updateProfile` method re-evaluates `is_complete` based on
whether `nickname`, `gender`, `birth_date`, `latitude`, and `longitude` are all 
present. But looking at the code at line 225-231:\n\n```typescript\nconst isComp
lete = !!(\n  updated.nickname &&\n  updated.gender &&\n  updated.birth_date &&\
n  updated.latitude != null &&\n  updated.longitude != null\n);\n```\n\nWait, bu
t the `createProfile` method also requires `avatar_url` (line 32-38), but `updat
eProfile` doesn\'t check for `avatar_url` when determining completeness. This mi
ght be a bug, but it\'s not the cause of our current issue.\n\nThe issue is that
after the E2E flow ran, `is_complete` is still 0. Let me check what data was act
ually sent to the backend. Maybe the mobile app didn\'t send `latitude` and `lon
gitude`.\n\nLooking at the profile setup page code:\n```dart\nvoid _pickLocation
() async {\n  setState(() {\n    _latitude = 31.2304;\n    _longitude = 121.4737
;\n  });\n}\n```\n\nAnd `_onSave()` creates the request:\n```dart\nfinal request
= UpdateProfileRequest(\n  nickname: _nicknameController.text.trim(),\n  gender:
_gender == \'male\' ? UpdateProfileRequestGenderEnum.male : ...,\n  birthDate: _
birthDate!,\n  latitude: _latitude!,\n  longitude: _longitude!,\n  avatarUrl: _a
vatarUrl,\n);\n```\n\nWait, if `_latitude` or `_longitude` is null, `_onSave()` 
would fail the null check and show a SnackBar. The flow shows it tapped "允许位
置授权" and then "完成", so `_latitude` and `_longitude` should be set.\n\nLet m
e check the API logs to see what request was actually sent. Or I can just query 
the database to see what fields were updated.\n\nActually, looking at the databa
se query result after running the flow:\n```\nis_complete: 0, nickname: NULL, ge
nder: NULL\n```\n\nThis means NOTHING was updated! The profile is still complete
ly empty. So the API call either:\n1. Never happened\n2. Failed\n3. The app cras
hed or errored out\n\nLet me check the API logs from when we ran the profile set
up flow. The API was running in the background. Let me look at the logs.\n\nActu
ally, wait - I stopped the API process and started a new one in the background e
arlier. Let me check if the API is still running and what its logs say.',
    encrypted=None
)
