relations: ["profile"],\n    });\n    const isNewUser = !user.profile || !user.p
rofile.is_complete;\n    return {\n      id: user.id,\n      phone: user.phone,\
n      is_new_user: isNewUser,\n      profile_complete: user.profile?.is_complet
e ?? false,\n    };\n}\n```\n\nThe backend correctly returns `profile_complete: 
false` when the profile is incomplete. But the app is still redirecting to the h
ome screen.\n\nLooking at the login page code, after successful login:\n```dart\
ncontext.read<AuthBloc>().add(LoginRequested(phone: phone, code: code));\n```\n\
nAnd in the auth bloc, if `is_new_user` is true, the app should navigate to prof
ile setup. Let me check the auth bloc and routing logic.\n\nActually, wait - may
be the auth bloc is checking `is_new_user` from the login response, not from `/a
uth/me`. The login response includes `is_new_user`:\n\n```typescript\nasync logi
n(phone: string, smsCode: string): Promise<AuthResponseDto> {\n    ...\n    cons
t { user, isNew } = await this.findOrCreateUser(phone);\n    const tokens = this
.generateTokens(user.id);\n    tokens.is_new_user = isNew;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nA
nd `findOrCreateUser` checks if the user already exists:\n```typescript\nasync f
indOrCreateUser(phone: string): Promise<{ user: UserEntity; isNew: boolean }> {\
n    let user = await this.userRepo.findOne({ where: { phone } });\n    let isNe
w = false;\n    if (!user) {\n      // create user\n      isNew = true;\n    }\n
   return { user, isNew };\n}\n```\n\nSo `is_new_user` in the login response is 
based on whether the user was JUST created, not whether their profile is complet
e. The test user "13800138000" already exists in the database (created during ea
rlier tests), so `is_new_user` is `false` in the login response.\n\nBut the app 
